# Quality Gates

## Before proposing "done"
- Ensure TypeScript correctness for changed code
- Run lint for impacted files/project scope when feasible
- Run relevant tests; add/update tests for behavior changes

## Testing policy
- New logic should include tests where practical
- Prefer behavior-focused tests (Testing Library + Vitest)
- Cover user-visible states (loading, error, empty, success)

## Code review posture
When asked to review code:
- Focus on correctness, regressions, architecture risks, and missing tests
- Provide concrete findings with severity and fixes
